article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 72, Middle Tennessee 65
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. -- Lester Hudson scored a game-high 28 points to lead Tennessee-Martin in a 72-65 win over Middle Tennessee on Monday night. Hudson hit 10 of 15 shots from the field and was 3-for-6 from beyond the arc. Delrico Lane dished out a game-high six assists. The Skyhawks (3-5) shot 52.1 percent from the field (25 of 48) for the game, in which they held off a second-half comeback attempt by the Blue Raiders (4-4) after leading by 11 points at halftime. Desmond Yates led the Blue Raiders with 21 points. Kevin Kanaskie added 16 points and sank 5 of 5 free throws, but was 1 of 10 on 3-pointers in the loss. Demetrius Green chipped in with 11 points. The Blue Raiders shot 42.9 percent in the game (24 of 56).
